{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I get asked a lot what the difference\nbetween my work is"},{"time":3691,"text":"and typical Pentagon\nlong-range strategic planners."},{"time":7000,"text":"And the answer I like to offer is"},{"time":8000,"text":"what they typically do is they think\nabout the future of wars"},{"time":11000,"text":"in the context of war."},{"time":13000,"text":"And what I've spent 15 years\ndoing in this business --"},{"time":16000,"text":"and it's taken me almost\n14 to figure it out --"},{"time":18263,"text":"is I think about the future of wars\nin the context of everything else."},{"time":23000,"text":"So I tend to specialize\non the scene between war and peace."},{"time":27000,"text":"The material I'm going to show\nyou is one idea from a book"},{"time":30000,"text":"with a lot of ideas."},{"time":31000,"text":"It's the one that takes me\naround the world right now"},{"time":33548,"text":"interacting with foreign\nmilitaries quite a bit."},{"time":36000,"text":"The material was generated\nin two years of work I did"},{"time":38000,"text":"for the Secretary of Defense,"},{"time":39000,"text":"thinking about a new\nnational grand strategy"},{"time":42000,"text":"for the United States."},{"time":43826,"text":"I'm going to present a problem"},{"time":45279,"text":"and try to give you an answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48000,"text":"Here's my favorite bonehead concept\nfrom the 1990s in the Pentagon:"},{"time":52000,"text":"the theory of anti-access,\narea-denial asymmetrical strategies."},{"time":56000,"text":"Why do we call it that?"},{"time":57000,"text":"Because it's got all those\nA's lined up I guess."},{"time":65000,"text":"This is gobbledygook for"},{"time":67000,"text":"if the United States fights\nsomebody we're going to be huge."},{"time":70000,"text":"They're going to be small."},{"time":71000,"text":"And if they try to fight us\nin the traditional, straight-up manner"},{"time":73000,"text":"we're going to kick their ass,"},{"time":74000,"text":"which is why people don't\ntry to do that any more."},{"time":77000,"text":"I met the last Air Force\nGeneral who had actually"},{"time":80000,"text":"shot down an enemy plane in combat."},{"time":82000,"text":"He's now a one star General."},{"time":84000,"text":"That's how distant\nwe are from even meeting an air force"},{"time":88000,"text":"willing to fly against ours."},{"time":90000,"text":"So that overmatched capability\ncreates problems --"},{"time":93000,"text":"catastrophic successes\nthe White House calls them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"And we're trying to figure that out,"},{"time":101000,"text":"because it is an amazing capability."},{"time":103000,"text":"The question is, what's the good\nyou can do with it?"},{"time":106000,"text":"OK?"},{"time":108000,"text":"The theory of anti-access, area-denial\nasymmetrical strategies --"},{"time":112000,"text":"gobbledygook that we sell to Congress,"},{"time":114000,"text":"because if we just told them\nwe can kick anybody's asses"},{"time":117000,"text":"they wouldn't buy us\nall the stuff we want."},{"time":119072,"text":"So we say, area-denial, anti-access\nasymmetrical strategies"},{"time":123000,"text":"and their eyes glaze over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"And they say, \"Will you\nbuild it in my district?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":137000,"text":"Here's my parody and it ain't much of one."},{"time":138000,"text":"Let's talk about a battle space."},{"time":139000,"text":"I don't know, Taiwan Straits 2025."},{"time":141000,"text":"Let's talk about an enemy embedded\nwithin that battle space."},{"time":144000,"text":"I don't know, the Million Man Swim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"The United States has to access\nthat battle space instantaneously."},{"time":152167,"text":"They throw up anti-access,\narea-denial asymmetrical strategies."},{"time":156000,"text":"A banana peel on the tarmac."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"Trojan horses on our computer networks"},{"time":161000,"text":"reveal all our Achilles' heels instantly."},{"time":164000,"text":"We say, \"China, it's yours.\""},{"time":166000,"text":"Prometheus approach, largely\na geographic definition,"},{"time":169000,"text":"focuses almost exclusively\non the start of conflict."},{"time":171000,"text":"We field the first-half team in a league"},{"time":173000,"text":"that insists on keeping score\nuntil the end of the game."},{"time":176000,"text":"That's the problem."},{"time":178000,"text":"We can run the score up against anybody,"},{"time":180000,"text":"and then get our asses\nkicked in the second half --"},{"time":182453,"text":"what they call fourth generation warfare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"Here's the way\nI like to describe it instead."},{"time":187167,"text":"There is no battle space the U.S.\nMilitary cannot access."},{"time":190000,"text":"They said we couldn't do Afghanistan.\nWe did it with ease."},{"time":192000,"text":"They said we couldn't do Iraq."},{"time":194000,"text":"We did it with 150 combat\ncasualties in six weeks."},{"time":198000,"text":"We did it so fast we weren't\nprepared for their collapse."},{"time":202000,"text":"There is nobody we can't take down."},{"time":205000,"text":"The question is, what do\nyou do with the power?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"So there's no trouble\naccessing battle spaces."},{"time":209215,"text":"What we have trouble accessing\nis the transition space"},{"time":212000,"text":"that must naturally follow,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and creating the peace space\nthat allows us to move on."},{"time":218000,"text":"Problem is, the Defense\nDepartment over here"},{"time":220120,"text":"beats the hell out of you."},{"time":222826,"text":"The State Department over here says,"},{"time":224565,"text":"\"Come on boy, I know you can make it.\""},{"time":226976,"text":"And that poor country runs off that ledge,"},{"time":229000,"text":"does that cartoon thing and then drops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"This is not about overwhelming\nforce, but proportional force."},{"time":239000,"text":"It's about non-lethal technologies,"},{"time":241000,"text":"because if you fire real ammo into a crowd"},{"time":244000,"text":"of women and children rioting"},{"time":246976,"text":"you're going to lose friends very quickly."},{"time":249000,"text":"This is not about projecting\npower, but about staying power,"},{"time":251882,"text":"which is about legitimacy with the locals."},{"time":254000,"text":"Who do you access in this\ntransition space?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":256072,"text":"You have to create internal partners.\nYou have to access coalition partners."},{"time":259716,"text":"We asked the Indians\nfor 17,000 peace keepers."},{"time":262000,"text":"I know their senior leadership,\nthey wanted to give it to us."},{"time":265000,"text":"But they said to us, \"You know what?"},{"time":267000,"text":"In that transition space you're\nmostly hat not enough cattle."},{"time":270826,"text":"We don't think you can pull it off,"},{"time":272000,"text":"we're not going to give you\nour 17,000 peace keepers for fodder.\""},{"time":274000,"text":"We asked the Russians for 40,000."},{"time":277000,"text":"They said no."},{"time":278000,"text":"I was in China in August, I said,"},{"time":279000,"text":"\"You should have 50,000\npeace keepers in Iraq."},{"time":282000,"text":"It's your oil, not ours.\""},{"time":285000,"text":"Which is the truth. It's their oil."},{"time":287000,"text":"And the Chinese said to me, \"Dr.\nBarnett, you're absolutely right."},{"time":290167,"text":"In a perfect world we'd have 50,000 there."},{"time":293000,"text":"But it's not a perfect world,"},{"time":295000,"text":"and your administration isn't\ngetting us any closer.\""},{"time":299000,"text":"But we have trouble\naccessing our outcomes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"We lucked out, frankly, on the selection."},{"time":304000,"text":"We face different opponents\nacross these three."},{"time":307000,"text":"And it's time to start admitting"},{"time":308000,"text":"you can't ask the same 19-year-old\nto do it all, day in and day out."},{"time":312000,"text":"It's just too damn hard."},{"time":314000,"text":"We have an unparalleled\ncapacity to wage war."},{"time":318000,"text":"We don't do the everything else so well."},{"time":321000,"text":"Frankly, we do it better than anybody\nand we still suck at it."},{"time":323000,"text":"We have a brilliant Secretary of War."},{"time":325000,"text":"We don't have a Secretary\nof Everything Else."},{"time":328000,"text":"Because if we did, that guy\nwould be in front of the Senate,"},{"time":330882,"text":"still testifying over Abu Ghraib."},{"time":333000,"text":"The problem is he doesn't exist."},{"time":336000,"text":"There is no Secretary of Everything Else."},{"time":339000,"text":"I think we have an unparalleled\ncapacity to wage war."},{"time":342000,"text":"I call that the Leviathan Force."},{"time":344000,"text":"What we need to build is a force\nfor the Everything Else."},{"time":346000,"text":"I call them the System Administrators."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"What I think this really represents"},{"time":350000,"text":"is lack of an A to Z rule set\nfor the world as a whole"},{"time":352000,"text":"for processing politically\nbankrupt states."},{"time":354072,"text":"We have one for processing\neconomically bankrupt states."},{"time":357000,"text":"It's the IMF Sovereign\nBankruptcy Plan, OK?"},{"time":361000,"text":"We argue about it every time we use it."},{"time":363000,"text":"Argentina just went through it,\nbroke a lot of rules."},{"time":365000,"text":"They got out on the far end, we said,\n\"Fine, don't worry about it.\""},{"time":368215,"text":"It's transparent. A certain\namount of certainty"},{"time":371000,"text":"gives the sense of a non-zero outcome."},{"time":373000,"text":"We don't have one for processing\npolitically bankrupt states"},{"time":375882,"text":"that, frankly, everybody wants gone."},{"time":378000,"text":"Like Saddam, like Mugabe,\nlike Kim Jong-Il --"},{"time":382000,"text":"people who kill in hundreds\nof thousands or millions."},{"time":386000,"text":"Like the 250,000 dead so far in Sudan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"What would an A to Z system look like?"},{"time":392000,"text":"I'm going to distinguish\nbetween what I call"},{"time":394120,"text":"front half and back half."},{"time":397000,"text":"And let's call this red line,\nI don't know, mission accomplished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"What we have extant right now,"},{"time":410000,"text":"at the beginning of this system, is the U.N.\nSecurity Council as a grand jury."},{"time":412000,"text":"What can they do?"},{"time":413000,"text":"They can indict your ass."},{"time":417000,"text":"They can debate it. They can\nwrite it on a piece of paper."},{"time":419000,"text":"They can put it in an envelope\nand mail it to you,"},{"time":421405,"text":"and then say in no uncertain\nterms, \"Please cut that out.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"That gets you about four million dead\nin Central Africa over the 1990s."},{"time":434405,"text":"That gets you 250,000 dead\nin the Sudan in the last 15 months."},{"time":438826,"text":"Everybody's got to answer\ntheir grandchildren some day"},{"time":440000,"text":"what you did\nabout the holocaust in Africa,"},{"time":443000,"text":"and you better have an answer."},{"time":448000,"text":"We don't have anything to translate\nthat will into action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452000,"text":"What we do have is the U.S.-enabled\nLeviathan Force that says,"},{"time":455000,"text":"\"You want me to take that guy down?\nI'll take that guy down."},{"time":458000,"text":"I'll do it on Tuesday. It will cost\nyou 20 billion dollars.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":461000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":466000,"text":"But here's the deal."},{"time":468000,"text":"As soon as I can't find\nanybody else to air out,"},{"time":470310,"text":"I leave the scene immediately."},{"time":472000,"text":"That's called the Powell Doctrine."},{"time":476000,"text":"Way downstream we have\nthe International Criminal Court."},{"time":478000,"text":"They love to put them on trial.\nThey've got Milosević right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480000,"text":"What are we missing?"},{"time":482000,"text":"A functioning executive\nthat will translate will into action,"},{"time":485000,"text":"because we don't have it."},{"time":487000,"text":"Every time we lead one of these efforts"},{"time":489000,"text":"we have to whip ourselves\ninto this imminent threat thing."},{"time":493000,"text":"We haven't faced an imminent threat since"},{"time":495000,"text":"the Cuban missile crisis in 1962."},{"time":497000,"text":"But we use this language from a bygone era"},{"time":498000,"text":"to scare ourselves into doing something"},{"time":501000,"text":"because we're a democracy\nand that's what it takes."},{"time":503453,"text":"And if that doesn't work\nwe scream, \"He's got a gun!\""},{"time":506001,"text":"just as we rush in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"And then we look over the body"},{"time":516000,"text":"and we find an old cigarette\nlighter and we say,"},{"time":518310,"text":"\"Jesus, it was dark.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":522000,"text":"Do you want to do it, France?"},{"time":524000,"text":"France says, \"No, but I do\nlike to criticize you after the fact.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":529000,"text":"What we need downstream\nis a great power enabled --"},{"time":532000,"text":"what I call that Sys Admin Force."},{"time":534000,"text":"We should have had 250,000\ntroops streaming into Iraq"},{"time":536000,"text":"on the heels of that Leviathan\nsweeping towards Baghdad."},{"time":539000,"text":"What do you get then?"},{"time":540000,"text":"No looting, no military disappearing,"},{"time":542000,"text":"no arms disappearing,\nno ammo disappearing,"},{"time":544072,"text":"no Muqtada Al-Sadr -- I'm\nwrecking his bones --"},{"time":546335,"text":"no insurgency."},{"time":548000,"text":"Talk to anybody who was over there\nin the first six months."},{"time":550000,"text":"We had six months to feel\nthe lob, to get the job done,"},{"time":553000,"text":"and we dicked around for six months."},{"time":555000,"text":"And then they turned on us."},{"time":557000,"text":"Why? Because they just got fed up."},{"time":559000,"text":"They saw what we did to Saddam."},{"time":561000,"text":"They said, \"You're that powerful,\nyou can resurrect this country."},{"time":563000,"text":"You're America.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":565000,"text":"What we need is an international\nreconstruction fund --"},{"time":567000,"text":"Sebastian Mallaby,\nWashington Post, great idea."},{"time":569263,"text":"Model on the IMF."},{"time":571000,"text":"Instead of passing the hat each time, OK?"},{"time":574000,"text":"Where are we going to find this guy?\nG20, that's easy."},{"time":577000,"text":"Check out their agenda since 9/11."},{"time":579000,"text":"All security dominated."},{"time":581000,"text":"They're going to decide up front\nhow the money gets spent"},{"time":583000,"text":"just like in the IMF."},{"time":584000,"text":"You vote according to how much\nmoney you put in the kitty."},{"time":587826,"text":"Here's my challenge\nto the Defense Department."},{"time":589000,"text":"You've got to build this force.\nYou've got to seed this force."},{"time":592000,"text":"You've got to track coalition partners.\nCreate a record of success."},{"time":595215,"text":"You will get this model."},{"time":597000,"text":"You tell me it's too hard to do."},{"time":599000,"text":"I'll walk this dog right\nthrough that six part series on the Balkans."},{"time":603000,"text":"We did it just like that."},{"time":605000,"text":"I'm talking about regularizing\nit, making it transparent."},{"time":607000,"text":"Would you like Mugabe gone?"},{"time":609000,"text":"Would you like Kim Jong-Il,\nwho's killed about two million people,"},{"time":611000,"text":"would you like him gone?"},{"time":614000,"text":"Would you like a better system?"},{"time":617000,"text":"This is why it matters to the military."},{"time":619000,"text":"They've been experiencing an identity\ncrisis since the end of the Cold War."},{"time":623000,"text":"I'm not talking about the difference\nbetween reality and desire,"},{"time":626072,"text":"which I can do because I'm\nnot inside the beltway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628477,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"I'm talking about the 1990s."},{"time":632000,"text":"The Berlin Wall falls. We do Desert Storm."},{"time":635000,"text":"The split starts to emerge\nbetween those in the military"},{"time":637000,"text":"who see a future they can live with,"},{"time":639000,"text":"and those who see a future\nthat starts to scare them,"},{"time":641000,"text":"like the U.S. submarine community,"},{"time":643000,"text":"which watches the Soviet\nNavy disappear overnight."},{"time":645405,"text":"Ah!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"So they start moving\nfrom reality towards desire"},{"time":653000,"text":"and they create their own special language"},{"time":655024,"text":"to describe their voyage of self-discovery\nand self-actualization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658191,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"The problem is you need a big,\nsexy opponent to fight against."},{"time":663000,"text":"And if you can't find\none you've got to make one up."},{"time":665501,"text":"China, all grown up, going to be a looker!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":668000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"The rest of the military got\ndragged down into the muck"},{"time":674000,"text":"across the 1990s"},{"time":675000,"text":"and they developed this very\nderisive term to describe it:"},{"time":677786,"text":"military operations other than war."},{"time":680000,"text":"I ask you, who joins the military\nto do things other than war?"},{"time":682977,"text":"Actually, most of them."},{"time":685000,"text":"Jessica Lynch never\nplanned on shooting back."},{"time":688000,"text":"Most of them don't pick up a rifle."},{"time":692000,"text":"I maintain this is code\ninside the Army for,"},{"time":694120,"text":"\"We don't want to do this.\""},{"time":698000,"text":"They spent the 1990s\nworking the messy scene"},{"time":700120,"text":"between globalized parts of the world"},{"time":702000,"text":"What I call the core and the gap."},{"time":707000,"text":"The Clinton administration wasn't\ninterested in running this."},{"time":709000,"text":"For eight years, after screwing\nup the relationship on day one --"},{"time":711000,"text":"inauguration day with gays\nin the military --"},{"time":714000,"text":"which was deft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":718000,"text":"So we were home alone for eight years."},{"time":720000,"text":"And what did we do home alone?"},{"time":722000,"text":"We bought one military\nand we operated another."},{"time":724263,"text":"It's like the guy who goes\nto the doctor and says,"},{"time":726668,"text":"\"Doctor, it hurts when I do this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":729000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":732000,"text":"The doctor says, \"Stop\ndoing that you idiot.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":735000,"text":"I used to give this brief\ninside the Pentagon in the early 1990s."},{"time":737000,"text":"I'd say, \"You're buying one military\nand you're operating another,"},{"time":739000,"text":"and eventually it's going to hurt.\nIt's wrong."},{"time":741215,"text":"Bad Pentagon, bad!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":743000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"And they'd say, \"Dr.\nBarnett, you are so right."},{"time":747263,"text":"Can you come back next year\nand remind us again?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":749621,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":755000,"text":"Some people say 9/11 heals the rift --"},{"time":757000,"text":"jerks the long-term transformation gurus"},{"time":760000,"text":"out of their 30,000 foot view of history,"},{"time":762000,"text":"drags them down in to the muck and says,\n\"You want a networked opponent?"},{"time":764000,"text":"I've got one, he's everywhere,\ngo find him.\""},{"time":767000,"text":"It elevates MOOTW --\nhow we pronounce that acronym --"},{"time":770000,"text":"from crap to grand strategy,"},{"time":773000,"text":"because that's how you're\ngoing to shrink that gap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"Some people put these two things together"},{"time":776000,"text":"and they call it empire, which I think\nis a boneheaded concept."},{"time":779024,"text":"Empire is about the enforcement\nof not just minimal rule sets,"},{"time":782001,"text":"which you cannot do,"},{"time":783000,"text":"but maximum rule sets which you must do."},{"time":785000,"text":"It's not our system of governance."},{"time":787000,"text":"Never how we've sought to interact\nwith the outside world."},{"time":789000,"text":"I prefer that phrase\nSystem Administration."},{"time":791072,"text":"We enforce the minimal rule sets"},{"time":793000,"text":"for maintaining connectivity\nto the global economy."},{"time":795453,"text":"Certain bad things you cannot do."},{"time":800000,"text":"How this impacts the way we think\nabout the future of war."},{"time":802000,"text":"This is a concept which gets me\nvilified throughout the Pentagon."},{"time":805120,"text":"It makes me very popular as well."},{"time":807000,"text":"Everybody's got an opinion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"Going back to the beginning\nof our country --"},{"time":811167,"text":"historically, defenses meant\nprotection of the homeland."},{"time":815000,"text":"Security has meant everything else."},{"time":818000,"text":"Written into our constitution,"},{"time":820000,"text":"two different forces,\ntwo different functions."},{"time":823000,"text":"Raise an army when you need it,"},{"time":825000,"text":"and maintain a navy\nfor day-to-day connectivity."},{"time":830000,"text":"A Department of War,\na Department of Everything Else."},{"time":834000,"text":"A big stick, a baton stick."},{"time":838000,"text":"Can of whup ass,"},{"time":841000,"text":"the networking force."},{"time":843000,"text":"In 1947 we merged these\ntwo things together"},{"time":845072,"text":"in the Defense Department."},{"time":847000,"text":"Our long-term rationale becomes,"},{"time":849000,"text":"we're involved in a hair trigger\nstand off with the Soviets."},{"time":852000,"text":"To attack America is to risk\nblowing up the world."},{"time":855000,"text":"We connected national security\nto international security"},{"time":859000,"text":"with about a seven minute time delay."},{"time":863000,"text":"That's not our problem now."},{"time":865000,"text":"They can kill\nthree million in Chicago tomorrow"},{"time":867263,"text":"and we don't go\nto the mattresses with nukes."},{"time":870000,"text":"That's the scary part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"The question is how do we reconnect\nAmerican national security"},{"time":876000,"text":"with global security to make\nthe world a lot more comfortable,"},{"time":880000,"text":"and to embed and contextualize\nour employment"},{"time":883000,"text":"of force around the planet?"},{"time":888000,"text":"What's happened\nsince is that bifurcation I described."},{"time":891826,"text":"We talked about this\ngoing all the way back"},{"time":893000,"text":"to the end of the Cold War."},{"time":895000,"text":"Let's have a Department of War,\nand a Department of Something Else."},{"time":897000,"text":"Some people say, \"Hell,\n9/11 did it for you.\""},{"time":901000,"text":"Now we've got a home\ngame and an away game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903072,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":909000,"text":"The Department of Homeland Security\nis a strategic feel good measure."},{"time":913000,"text":"It's going to be the Department\nof Agriculture for the 21st century."},{"time":917000,"text":"TSA -- thousands standing around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":926846,"text":"I supported the war in Iraq."},{"time":928846,"text":"He was a bad guy with multiple priors."},{"time":930846,"text":"It's not like we had to find him"},{"time":932846,"text":"actually killing somebody\nlive to arrest him."},{"time":937846,"text":"I knew we'd kick ass in the war\nwith the Leviathan Force."},{"time":940537,"text":"I knew we'd have a hard\ntime with what followed."},{"time":942846,"text":"But I know this organization doesn't\nchange until it experiences failure."},{"time":946846,"text":"What do I mean by these\ntwo different forces?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":949846,"text":"This is the Hobbesian Force."},{"time":951846,"text":"I love this force. I don't\nwant to see it go."},{"time":953846,"text":"That plus nukes rules out great power war."},{"time":955846,"text":"This is the military the rest\nof the world wants us to build."},{"time":957846,"text":"It's why I travel all over the world\ntalking to foreign militaries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":961061,"text":"What does this mean?"},{"time":963846,"text":"It means you've got to stop pretending"},{"time":965846,"text":"you can do these two very disparate\nskill sets with the same 19-year-old."},{"time":969347,"text":"Switching back, morning,\nafternoon, evening,"},{"time":971846,"text":"morning, afternoon, eveni